ot only the changing lives of villagers, but also the state regulations and territorialization projects that drove these changes on the outskirts of Hanoi, and the early urban changes in the decades that preceded the reforms and continue to influence the area's urbanization. Despite the new buildings, the end of farming activities, and the arrival of a large new population, the former villagers still consider Hoa Muc their homeland. The compelling story of this single village is both a portrait of a population that has endured despite drastic upheavals and a new analytical window onto Vietnam's ongoing urban transition.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCity planningzVietnamzHanoixHistoryy20th century. 0aCity planningzVietnamzHanoixHistoryy21st century. 0aLand tenurexPolitical aspectszVietnamzHanoixHistoryy20th century. 0aLand tenurexPolitical aspectszVietnamzHanoixHistoryy21st century. 0aUrbanizationzVietnamzHanoixHistoryy20th century. 0aUrbanizationzVietnamzHanoixHistoryy21st century. 7aHISTORY / Asia / Southeast Asia.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2013z978311127412608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2013z978311127715808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311141860540uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077482669340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774826693423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774826693/original  a978-3-11-127412-6  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2013b2013  a978-3-11-127715-8  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2013b2013  a978-3-11-141860-5  University of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000c2013d2000  aGBV-deGruyter-alles